description: U.S. and German authorities foiled a Russian assassination plot against Armin Papperger, CEO of Rheinmetall, a German arms firm that makes weapons for Ukraine.
title: Russia plotted to kill CEO of German firm that makes weapons for Ukraine, sources say

description: A statue of Anne Frank, the young Jewish girl who hid along with other Jewish people for nearly two years in a secret annex in Amsterdam during the Holocaust before they were detained, was defaced with "Gaza" graffiti, sparking immediate outrage.
title: Anne Frank statue in Amsterdam vandalized with 'Gaza' graffiti

description: Estonian Jaan Roose, a Hollywood stuntman, became the first person to do a slackline walk over Strait of Messina, which separates Sicily from the Italian mainland.
title: Watch: Man crosses from Italian mainland to Sicily on a slackline

description: Taiwan said it responded to four Chinese coast guard ships that were sailing in prohibited waters near the Taiwanese-controlled island of Kinmen. In response to the alleged intrusion of its waters, Taiwan said it dispatched four of its own coast guard vessels to conduct one-on-one monitoring alongside the four Chinese ships.
title: Taiwan Coast Guard monitors Chinese military vessels in South China Sea

description: NATO has openly accused China of having a much more important role in Russia's war in Ukraine than it previously claimed, including supplying components for military equipment and chemicals for explosives. NBC News' Claudio Lavanga reports for Early Today.
title: NATO rebukes China as a 'decisive enabler' of Russia and its war in Ukraine

description: The second Copa America semifinal took a violent turn Wednesday when Uruguayan players brawled with fans in the stands following their elimination at the hands of Colombia.
title: Uruguayan players brawl with Colombia fans following Copa America semifinal loss

description: A 26-year-old man, who is suspected of a triple murder, was arrested in the U.K. The victims are all women and are all believed to belong to the same family, according to U.K. police. Authorities believe that a crossbow, among other weapons, was used.
title: 26-year-old suspect of triple murder arrested in U.K.
